complete <- ChickWeight %>% group_by(Chick) %>% mutate(n = n()) %>% filter(n() == 12)
print(head(complete, 3))
## # A tibble: 3 x 5
## # Groups:   Chick [1]
##   weight  Time Chick Diet      n
##    <dbl> <dbl> <ord> <fct> <int>
## 1     42     0 1     1        12
## 2     51     2 1     1        12
## 3     59     4 1     1        12
complete <- complete %>% group_by(Chick) %>% mutate(weightgain = weight[Time == Time] - weight[Time == 0])
